to Internet freedom,

01:52:19.800 --> 01:52:22.598
to basic political liberty,
not only in the United States,

01:52:22.680 --> 01:52:24.716
but all around the world.

01:52:24.840 --> 01:52:28.515
And he felt it was his duty as
a human being to disclose it.

01:52:39.320 --> 01:52:42.551
Uh, my name's Ed Snowden.
I'm 29 years old.

01:52:42.640 --> 01:52:44.073
I work for
Booz Allen Hamilton

01:52:44.160 --> 01:52:47.675
as an infrastructure analyst
for NSA in Hawaii.

01:52:58.240 --> 01:53:00.470
The identity of the man
who sent the Obama...

01:53:00.560 --> 01:53:04.758
You can't come forward against the
most powerful intelligence agencies

01:53:04.880 --> 01:53:07.440
in the world without expecting
to have some risk.

01:53:07.520 --> 01:53:09.590
They're just such
powerful adversaries.

01:53:09.720 --> 01:53:12.598
So no one can
meaningfully oppose them.

01:53:12.720 --> 01:53:13.789
He did it.

01:53:13.880 --> 01:53:16.713
You know, if they want to get you,
they will get you, in time.

01:53:16.800 --> 01:53:17.800
The kid did it!

01:53:17.880 --> 01:53:19.816
And it's just gonna get
worse for the next generation,

01:53:19.840 --> 01:53:21.193
as they extend
the capabilities

01:53:21.280 --> 01:53:24.795
of this sort of
architecture of oppression.

01:53:24.880 --> 01:53:29.192
And you realize that you might
be willing to accept any risk,

01:53:29.320 --> 01:53:33.029
as long as the public is able
to make their own decision

01:53:33.160 --> 01:53:34.752
about how
this is applied.

01:53:35.000 --> 01:53:37.719
Because even if you haven
't done anything wrong,

01:53:37.800 --> 01:53:39.756
you're being
watched and recorded.

01:53:41.080 --> 01:53:44.231
Look, I had access to the
entire intelligence community.

01:53:44.320 --> 01:53:47.551
So, if I had wanted
to harm the U. S.,

01:53:47.640 --> 01:53:51.872
you could shut down the entire
surveillance system in an afternoon.

01:53:51.960 --> 01:53:55.236
But that was never
my intention.

01:53:55.320 --> 01:53:58.392
And I think anybody
that's making that argument,

01:53:58.480 --> 01:54:02.837
they have to think,
if they were in my position,

01:54:02.920 --> 01:54:06.674
living in Hawaii, in paradise,
and making a ton of money,

01:54:06.760 --> 01:54:11.629
what would it take to make
you leave everything behind?

01:54:12.680 --> 01:54:17.356
The fear that I think I have
most in regards to the outcome

01:54:17.440 --> 01:54:20.193
for America of
these disclosures

01:54:20.280 --> 01:54:22.475
is that nothing
will change.

01:54:22.560 --> 01:54:26.348
In the coming months and the coming
years, it'll just get worse.

01:54:26.440 --> 01:54:29.000
And then eventually,
at some point,

01:54:29.080 --> 01:54:33.153
some new leader
will be elected

01:54:33.240 --> 01:54:37.119
who flips the switch,

01:54:37.200 --> 01:54:44.038
and the people won't be able to do
anything, by that point, to oppose it.

01:54:44.920 --> 01:54:47.070
And it'll be
turnkey tyranny.

01:54:49.040 --> 01:54:50.200
How you holding up?

01:54:51.120 --> 01:54:53.270
Yeah, I'll be fine.

01:54:54.120 --> 01:54:55.696
It's you guys that have
to start watching out

01:54:55.720 --> 01:54:57.199
for yourselves now.

01:54:58.360 --> 01:55:00.874
You know, if you have
any reason to believe

01:55:00.960 --> 01:55:05.556
that you're about to be raided or
intercepted or breached in any way,

01:55:05.640 --> 01:55:10.191
you format and destroy
all the data immediately.

01:55:10.280 --> 01:55:13.238
You have
the encrypted backups.

01:55:14.120 --> 01:55:15.439
And now, I...

01:55:18.440 --> 01:55:21.352
I no longer have any access
to these files myself.

01:55:21.440 --> 01:55:23.078
You guys have them all.

01:55:25.120 --> 01:55:26.189
Uh...

01:55:26.680 --> 01:55:29.478
Keep the focus on the stories,
that's all that matters.

01:55:31.520 --> 01:55:33.158
If you'll excuse me, it's...

01:55:35.920 --> 01:55:38.070
I think we should all get some rest.
We can use it.

01:55:38.360 --> 01:55:41.432
Yeah. I should probably
lay down on a soft bed

01:55:41.520 --> 01:55:43.556
while I still have
one available, right?

01:55:45.200 --> 01:55:47.077
You rest well.
Thank you.

01:55:49.280 --> 01:55:50.713
See you tomorrow.
Good night.

01:56:21.160 --> 01:56:23.355
Can you at least tell me
where you're going?

01:56:48.240 --> 01:56:49.798
Listen,
I know that I'm...

01:57:08.160 --> 01:57:09.752
Ewen, I'm on
the second floor.

01:57:11.280 --> 01:57:12.599
I don't see Tibbo.

01:57:14.960 --> 01:57:17.235
No. No, no, wait.
Okay. I think I see him.

01:57:18.120 --> 01:57:19.235
Shit!

01:57:19.880 --> 01:57:22.269
There's press swarming
all over the hotel.

01:57:22.360 --> 01:57:24.032
Yeah, I don't know.
I'll figure it out.

01:57:24.120 --> 01:57:26.160
I'll stop them with a press
conference or something.

01:57:26.280 --> 01:57:30.193
Hey, I'm Glenn.
Look, we really appreciate this.

01:57:30.280 --> 01:57:32.416
We understand you're one of the
best lawyers in Hong Kong.

01:57:32.440 --> 01:57:33.475
We'll do our best.

01:57:33.560 --> 01:57:36.518
We're gonna take him to the UN first,
then I prefer not to reveal.

01:57:36.600 --> 01:57:37.600
I understand.

01:57:37.640 --> 01:57:39.915
Shit. They spotted me.
You guys get going.

01:57:43.640 --> 01:57:45.296
Okay, I will take your questions
in an orderly fashion.

01:57:45.320 --> 01:57:46.456
Where is Snowden?
Do you know where he is?

01:57:46.480 --> 01:57:48.136
Come on,
please let us know!

01:57:48.160 --> 01:57:49.229
Did you get them?

01:57:49.320 --> 01:57:50.912
Yeah, this is the best
I could do.

01:57:51.040 --> 01:57:53.600
You're meeting Tibbo
in five minutes,

01:57:53.680 --> 01:57:56.194
on the skybridge
opposite the large mall.

01:57:59.960 --> 01:58:04.192
I've met a lot of astonishing
people in my life, but you...

01:58:06.400 --> 01:58:08.675
Okay, laddie.
Off you go.

01:58:09.640 --> 01:58:11.119
I won't let you down.

01:58:13.280 --> 01:58:15.794
You'd make a shitty journalist
without a camera.

01:58:16.680 --> 01:58:18.432
Are you sure?
Yeah.

01:58:18.880 --> 01:58:21.792
Okay. That's a great idea.

01:58:23.680 --> 01:58:24.680
Thanks.

01:58:27.040 --> 01:58:29.156
Oh! You don't want to
leave your luck behind.

01:58:29.720 --> 01:58:30.720
Oh.

01:58:30.960 --> 01:58:32.837
I think I'd like you
to have that.

01:58:35.040 --> 01:58:37.270
Thanks for everything.

01:58:37.960 --> 01:58:39.029
Thank you.

01:59:02.720 --> 01:59:04.200
I have
a van on the street.

01:59:09.240 --> 01:59:12.391
NSA leaker Edward
Snowden has now been charged formally

01:59:12.480 --> 01:59:17.235
with espionage, theft, and
conversion of government property.

01:59:17.360 --> 01:59:19.176
U. S. officials have asked Hong Kong

01:59:19.200 --> 01:59:20.713
to detain
the former contractor

01:59:20.840 --> 01:59:22.637
on a provisional
arrest warrant.

01:59:22.720 --> 01:59:24.836
Snowden has been
in Hong Kong since May...

01:59:24.920 --> 01:59:28.117
...remember, that
was back reportedly on May 20th.

01:59:28.760 --> 01:59:31.376
...Snowden has checked
out of the luxury hotel in Hong Kong,

01:59:31.400 --> 01:59:32.628
where he had been holed up.

01:59:35.800 --> 01:59:36.896
You might
turn your eyes away.

01:59:36.920 --> 01:59:38.416
...not likely
take action against him

01:59:38.440 --> 01:59:39.496
without an arrest
warrant from the U. S.

01:59:39.520 --> 01:59:42.216
The Justice Department
had to go to Interpol so that Snowden,

01:59:42.240 --> 01:59:44.496
if he tried to cross a border,
he could be intercepted and detained.

01:59:44.520 --> 01:59:45.976
Snowden is still in hiding.

01:59:46.000 --> 01:59:47.000
So again...

01:59:47.080 --> 01:59:48.816
But the
Americans are now closing in.

01:59:48.840 --> 01:59:50.990
They almost certainly know
where he is,

01:59:51.120 --> 01:59:53.714
they just need Hong Kong's
approval to get him.

01:59:53.800 --> 01:59:55.576
The Hong
Kong government does have

01:59:55.600 --> 01:59:57.636
an extradition agreement
with Washington.

01:59:57.720 --> 01:59:58.840
But the ultimate decision...

01:59:58.960 --> 02:00:02.350
So the big
question here is, where is he now?

02:00:04.960 --> 02:00:08.157
Thank you.
This is Ed. Ed, Mayana.

02:00:08.240 --> 02:00:09.912
Hi, Ed. Welcome.
Thank you.

02:00:10.320 --> 02:00:11.878
Thank you.

02:00:12.800 --> 02:00:14.711
These are good people.
They won't talk.

02:00:15.360 --> 02:00:18.158
I've been handling their cases for years.
They're like you.

02:00:18.240 --> 02:00:19.434
That's so nice.

02:00:19.760 --> 02:00:21.637
They're stateless.
Yeah.

02:00:22.120 --> 02:00:25.556
So we're waiting on the UN
application for refugee status.

02:00:25.640 --> 02:00:26.755
Yeah.

02:00:26.840 --> 02:00:29.673
Just in case you're arrested,
this is where you can call me.

02:00:29.760 --> 02:00:30.795
Yeah.

02:00:32.960 --> 02:00:34.109
Good.

02:00:34.800 --> 02:00:36.119
Thank you so much.

02:00:40.320 --> 02:00:44.996
You may not feel it,
Ed, but you're not alone.

02:00:45.880 --> 02:00:46.949
Thank you.

02:00:49.520 --> 02:00:51.696
...his longtime
girlfriend, Lindsay Mills,

02:00:51.720 --> 02:00:52.914
an amateur photographer,

02:00:53.000 --> 02:00:54.399
has not been heard from.

02:00:54.480 --> 02:00:56.391
It's believed
she's in seclusion

02:00:56.480 --> 02:00:57.993
in her parents' home
in Maryland,

02:00:58.080 --> 02:00:59.911
and has been questioned
by the FBI

02:01:00.000 --> 02:01:01.911
and remains
under investigation.

02:01:03.840 --> 02:01:07.594
Ten days have now gone by,
as the world looks for Edward Snowden.

02:01:07.680 --> 02:01:11.070
Rumors have surfaced that a rich
supporter is hiding Snowden

02:01:11.200 --> 02:01:14.510
somewhere in the Hong Kong
hills in a private mansion.

02:01:46.560 --> 02:01:48.915
It is now
confirmed that Edward Snowden

02:01:49.000 --> 02:01:51.309
has boarded a flight
from Hong Kong to Moscow.

02:01:51.400 --> 02:01:53.336
The State
Department is very disappointed

02:01:53.360 --> 02:01:54.952
in the authorities
in Hong Kong

02:01:55.040 --> 02:01:56.678
for letting Snowden go.

02:01:56.760 --> 02:01:59.376
He was accompanied
by a representative from WikiLeaks.

02:01:59.400 --> 02:02:02.551
Snowden is trying
to make his way from Russia to Cuba,

02:02:02.640 --> 02:02:04.835
and then to Ecuador
for political asylum.

02:02:04.960 --> 02:02:07.216
Moscow airport
officials say he won't be permitted

02:02:07.240 --> 02:02:08.639
to make his connective flight

02:02:08.720 --> 02:02:11.154
because the U. S. government
has revoked his passport.

02:02:11.240 --> 02:02:13.959
The United States
Secretary of State, John Kerry,

02:02:14.040 --> 02:02:17.919
outraged that Russia is refusing
to arrest the American fugitive.

02:02:18.000 --> 02:02:22.152
Now a man without a country
stranded inside the Moscow airport.

02:02:22.240 --> 02:02:24.913
No, I'm not gonna
be scrambling jets, uh,

02:02:25.000 --> 02:02:29.596
to get a 29-year-old hacker.

02:02:31.160 --> 02:02:32.696
The
President of Bolivia's plane

02:02:32.720 --> 02:02:34.995
was forced down in
Austria airspace today

02:02:35.080 --> 02:02:39.358
following U. S. suspicions that
Snowden may have been on board.

02:02:39.440 --> 02:02:41.795
After
39 days in the airport hotel,

02:02:41.880 --> 02:02:44.314
he's left with his Russian
lawyer and a legal advisor

02:02:44.400 --> 02:02:46.516
from WikiLeaks,
Sarah Harrison.

02:02:47.400 --> 02:02:50.198
He can now enjoy
all of the sweet, sweet liberty

02:02:50.280 --> 02:02:53.431
allowed under the regime
of President Vladimir Putin.

02:02:53.520 --> 02:02:56.717
There is still
a thing called execution.

02:02:56.800 --> 02:02:58.176
Mr. Snowden
actually deserves asylum

02:02:58.200 --> 02:02:59.474
and protection
around the globe.

02:02:59.600 --> 02:03:02.717
But he does have asylum
in Russia at least.

02:03:02.800 --> 02:03:04.791
He can engage in
the debate he started.

02:03:05.440 --> 02:03:06.714
And the world
now has an example

02:03:06.800 --> 02:03:08.040
that you can do
the right thing,

02:03:08.120 --> 02:03:11.874
and you don't have to end up
in a cage, one room, a prison.

02:03:13.960 --> 02:03:17.157
After more than a year
in the country under temporary asylum,

02:03:17.240 --> 02:03:21.631
Edward Snowden has received a
three-year residency permit in Russia.

02:03:30.000 --> 02:03:33.037
And now,
here live from Moscow,

02:03:33.320 --> 02:03:34.912
Edward Snowden.

02:03:36.280 --> 02:03:38.157
Hi, Ed. How you doing?

02:03:43.560 --> 02:03:44.993
Thank you.

02:03:45.640 --> 02:03:47.995
Uh, forgive me if I get my
bearings a little bit here.

02:03:48.080 --> 02:03:50.548
People always said
I was kind of a robot.

02:03:52.040 --> 02:03:54.554
How is it that
you came to be in Russia?

02:03:55.160 --> 02:03:56.912
Well, I never intended
to come here.

02:03:57.000 --> 02:04:00.913
You know, my passport was revoked
en route to Latin America.

02:04:01.000 --> 02:04:03.639
So when people say,
"Why are you in Russia?"

02:04:03.720 --> 02:04:06.598
I say,
"Ask the State Department."

02:04:07.520 --> 02:04:11.035
Does that mean you're willing
to go back and face trial?

02:04:11.720 --> 02:04:15.633
Absolutely, if it was
a fair and public trial.

02:04:16.280 --> 02:04:19.033
Unfortunately, that's not
what would happen right now,

02:04:19.120 --> 02:04:23.193
as long as the Espionage Act is
being used against whistleblowers.

02:04:24.560 --> 02:04:26.516
Do you still
think it was worth it?

02:04:26.600 --> 02:04:27.635
Yes, I do.

02:04:27.720 --> 02:04:31.633
Without the information
to start a public debate,

02:04:31.720 --> 02:04:33.119
we're lost.
You know...

02:04:33.720 --> 02:04:37.269
The people being able
to question our government

02:04:37.360 --> 02:04:39.954
and hold it accountable,

02:04:40.040 --> 02:04:44.955
that's the principle that the United
States of America was founded on.

02:04:45.080 --> 02:04:48.789
So if we want to protect
our national security,

02:04:48.880 --> 02:04:51.314
we should be protecting
that principle.

02:04:52.960 --> 02:04:55.235
What if your
argument falls on deaf ears?

02:04:55.320 --> 02:04:57.629
What if our leaders
don't act?

02:04:58.440 --> 02:05:01.671
I believe that,
if nothing changes,

02:05:02.680 --> 02:05:07.231
more and more people all over
the world will come forward.

02:05:07.920 --> 02:05:12.914
Whistleblowers and journalists,
but also regular citizens.

02:05:13.760 --> 02:05:19.596
And when those in power try to
hide by classifying everything,

02:05:20.360 --> 02:05:23.193
we will call them out on it.

02:05:23.720 --> 02:05:29.477
And when they try to scare us into
sacrificing our basic human rights,

02:05:29.560 --> 02:05:31.835
we won't be intimidated,

02:05:31.960 --> 02:05:36.590
and we won't give up,
and we will not be silenced.

02:05:38.240 --> 02:05:40.071
You're alone in
a foreign country,

02:05:40.160 --> 02:05:43.391
you'll be extradited
if you try to leave.

02:05:43.480 --> 02:05:45.152
That must be hard.

02:05:57.680 --> 02:06:01.229
When I left Hawaii,
I lost everything.

02:06:04.880 --> 02:06:06.836
And I had a stable life.

02:06:09.880 --> 02:06:11.996
A stable love.

02:06:12.080 --> 02:06:13.991
Family. Future.

02:06:15.800 --> 02:06:17.631
And I lost that life,

02:06:20.600 --> 02:06:22.636
but I've gained
a new one,

02:06:25.120 --> 02:06:26.951
and I'm incredibly
fortunate.

02:06:29.400 --> 02:06:30.719
And I think

02:06:32.720 --> 02:06:34.160
the greatest freedom
that I've gained

02:06:34.240 --> 02:06:37.835
is the fact that I no longer have to
worry about what happens tomorrow,

02:06:37.920 --> 02:06:40.309
because I'm happy with
what I've done today.

02:06:45.920 --> 02:06:48.753
Live from the Internet,
Edward Snowden!

02:08:06.760 --> 02:08:08.456
Has your
mindset changed about him?

02:08:08.480 --> 02:08:12.553
Is he now more whistleblower
than he is a, uh, hacker?

02:08:49.960 --> 02:08:51.976
What is going
to happen to Edward Snowden?

02:08:52.000 --> 02:08:54.719
He's going to die in Moscow.
He's not coming home.

02:09:32.800 --> 02:09:34.995
Edward Snowden,
is he a traitor or a hero?

02:09:35.120 --> 02:09:38.351
He stole
very important information.

02:09:56.960 --> 02:09:58.336
We have
breaking news tonight...

02:09:58.360 --> 02:09:59.360
Among the reforms,

02:09:59.440 --> 02:10:02.113
work with Congress to change how
the NSA collects phone records.

02:10:03.320 --> 02:10:05.754
Mandate more transparency
by the secret court

02:10:05.840 --> 02:10:07.910
that regularly approves
the surveillance.

02:10:09.840 --> 02:10:11.796
Well, is it
a victory for Edward Snowden?

02:10:11.880 --> 02:10:13.720
That's gonna depend
on the eye of the beholder.

02:10:15.520 --> 02:10:17.936
The American
government was acting illegally.

02:10:17.960 --> 02:10:21.200
I don't think he should
be brought home without facing the music.

02:10:22.960 --> 02:10:24.757
Snowden played
a very important role

02:10:24.840 --> 02:10:26.990
in educating
the American people

02:10:27.080 --> 02:10:31.471
to the degree in which our civil
liberties and our constitutional rights

02:10:31.560 --> 02:10:32.709
are being undermined.

